The product type segment of the wellness supplements market comprises dietary supplements, functional foods, and herbal supplements. Dietary supplements, such as vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and enzymes, play a crucial role in providing essential nutrients that may be lacking in the diet. Consumers turn to dietary supplements to bridge nutritional gaps and support overall health and well-being. Functional foods, on the other hand, go beyond basic nutrition and offer additional health benefits or targeted functionalities. These products are often fortified with specific nutrients or bioactive compounds known to promote health. Herbal supplements, derived from plant extracts and botanical sources, have gained popularity for their natural and holistic approach to health. Consumers seek herbal supplements for a variety of reasons, including immune support, stress relief, and improved overall wellness.

The distribution channel segment of the wellness supplements market plays a crucial role in reaching consumers and driving sales. Online retail has emerged as a significant channel for wellness supplements, offering consumers convenience, a wide product selection, and the ability to compare prices and read reviews before making a purchase. Specialty stores cater specifically to health and wellness products, creating a curated shopping experience for consumers seeking supplements and other wellness products. Pharmacies and supermarkets/hypermarkets remain important distribution channels for wellness supplements, providing a one-stop shop for consumers looking to purchase supplements along with other everyday essentials.

